-- South African Coal Prices Decline to Lowest Level in Six Weeks
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-03-05T09:50:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-05/south-african-coal-prices-decline-to-lowest-level-in-six-weeks.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, declined to the lowest level in six weeks.  Prices (CLSPSARB)  fell $1.76, or 1.7 percent, to $104.35 a metric ton
in the week ended March 2, the least since Jan. 20, according to
IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
